## Python Auto Backup Script

A simple **cross-platform backup script** written in Python.  
It creates **timestamped backups** of a given folder and stores them in a destination folder as either **.zip** or **.tar.gz** archives.  
Old backups are automatically deleted if they exceed a set limit.

---

## âœ¨ Features
- ğŸ”¹ Cross-platform (Windows, macOS, Linux).
- ğŸ”¹ Choose between `.zip` (Windows-friendly) or `.tar.gz` (Linux/macOS).
- ğŸ”¹ Automatically cleans up old backups (keeps only the latest ones).
- ğŸ”¹ Easy-to-edit config at the top of the script.
- ğŸ”¹ Simple, lightweight, no external dependencies.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Requirements
